**********AWS Infrastructure Automation with Terraform**********
Welcome to my Terraform project repository! This project is focused on automating the deployment of AWS infrastructure, significantly enhancing efficiency and scalability. 

Project Overview
This repository contains Terraform scripts to automate the creation of AWS resources, including:

VPCs
Subnets
Route Tables
Internet Gateways
Elastic IPs
NAT Gateways

Highlights:
Automated VPC Creation: Defined VPC architecture with subnets, route tables, and an Internet Gateway.
Efficient NAT Gateway Deployment: Simplified NAT Gateway setup for seamless internet access.
Dynamic Elastic IP Allocation: Automated management of Elastic IPs, ensuring resource control and flexibility.

Why Use Terraform?
Terraform is an open-source infrastructure as code software tool that provides a consistent CLI workflow to manage hundreds of cloud services. By using Terraform, we can:
Save Time: Automate repetitive tasks and streamline infrastructure setup.
Enhance Consistency: Ensure your infrastructure is provisioned consistently across environments.
Enable Scalability: Easily scale your infrastructure with minimal manual intervention.
